<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 8600 - ADJUSTMENTS - fender mounted mirrors- remove</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>fender mounted mirrors- remove</title>
        <para>Fender mounted mirror assemblies are mounted on the forward section of the fender assembly (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0900864">Figure 64, Items 3 and 4</hotlnk>) with a lateral mounting brace attached to the
            side of the hood section. The mirror assemblies are bolted to the hood and fender assemblies.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0900864" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900864.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 64. Fender Mounted Mirror (Passenger Side Shown)</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. MIRROR HEAD</callout1>
                <callout1>2. HOOD</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SIDE LATERAL BRACE</callout1>
                <callout1>4. MIRROR FENDER MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>5. FENDER SECTION</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Tilt the hood and fender assembly forward to access the mounting bolts for the nuts and flat
                washers.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f0900865" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900865.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 65. Fender Mounted Mirror Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. LATERAL MIRROR MOUNTING BRACE</callout1>
                <callout1>2. FENDER MOUNTING BRACKET BOLT</callout1>
                <callout1>3. FENDER SECTION</callout1>
                <callout1>4. MIRROR HEAD</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the lock nut and flat washer on the underside of the fender section. Secure the lock
                nut and flat washer and loosen (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900865">Figure 65, Item 2</hotlnk>) the mounting bolts in the mounting bracket on the
                outside fender section.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the lock nut and washer on the inside vertical section of the hood assembly. Loosen
                the mounting bolt in the lateral bracket base (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900865">Figure 65, Item 1</hotlnk>). It would be advisable to have an assistant steady
                the mirror during the removal process and to prevent breakage if the mirror should fall.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the mirror assembly and brackets.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Follow the same procedure to remove the opposite side mirror assembly.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
